    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-30T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-30T20:00:00-05:00" n="590"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d590">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/10345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Linnell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-01T09:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 1, 1937—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Canton River closed to navigation from 6 a.m. today by order of Military
                    Headquarters. While river continues closed Canton-Hong Kong Railway offers only
                    means of transportation between the two cities. It is officially stated,
                    however, that a motor road is being constructed and is expected to be completed
                    soon.</p>
                <p>Hong Kong mail to Swatow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Linnell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
